				posted 2004-10-16 09:01&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=11490"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=11477"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	It's probably simple mathematics actually (I've never played Targoid so I have to say probably).<br />
<br />
Let's try an example:<br />
<br />
A Targoid player is generating 10,000,000 PP per turn for building ships.<br />
<br />
Non-Organic Doomstars:<br />
<br />
23,716,000/10,000,000 = 2.3716  or  3 turns<br />
<br />
Organic Doomstars:<br />
<br />
(23,716,000 * 0.9)/10,000,000 = 2.13444  or  3 turns<br />
<br />
Notice that even though the organic doomstars are building 10% faster, it still takes three turns according to what is reported on the Ship Building page.  That is because Archspace always rounds up to the next whole number.<br />
<br />
So, how can you test to see if your organic dooms are actually being turned out 10% faster?  There are several ways, I will describe the easiest here:<br />
<br />
1) Delete all scheduled ships to be built from the Ship Building queue.  And wait a full turn for the funds to go to zero.<br />
<br />
2) Schedule to build roughly twice as many gunboats as you can build in a single turn.<br />
<br />
3) At the end of the turn, count how many gunboats were actually built (make sure that there are still gunboats left to be built in the queue - if there aren't then you didn't schedule enough to be built and need to try again).<br />
<br />
4) After counting the gunboats and verifying that you still had more to go, delete the remaining gunboats from the Ship Building queue and scrap the gunboats that you built (you really don't want the extra fluff).<br />
<br />
5) Wait another full turn for the Ship Building pool to go back to zero.<br />
<br />
6) Schedule the other type of gunboat to be build (enough for two turns).<br />
<br />
7) After one turn count the gunboats actually built.  The difference between the two builds should be roughly 10%.  In most cases it won't be exactly 10% because of the granularity of the test, but it should show you if your organic ships are building 10% faster or not.  Don't forget to cancel the remaining gunboats and scrap the ones you built.<br />
<br />
Now, after going through this long discussion, I have saved the best advice for last.  Don't bother with organic armor except for specific missions (and even then it isn't recommended).  The extra 10% doesn't make up for the lousy survivability.  And since you are Targoid, races like Evintos, Techanoid, Xeloss, and Bosalian will fire before you do and rip you apart if they have their commanders carefully chosen and leveled up (Cyber Scan Unit or Mental Giant).  The only time I'd recommend it is if you are guaranteed of fighting against a player armed almost exclusively with Distortion Blaster, but if you win, will you be guaranteed of meeting such an opponent next time you engage in battle?  Of course, once you have 40 fleets of 40 dooms each, it does make sense to have a few of these just for such circumstances.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
