				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=11498"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=11477"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Okay, here goes for those of you that are still confused.<br />
<br />
Doomstars have shielding of 6835.  With modifiers that can be almost doubled for most races if they build both shield boosting devices and have a level 20 shield system specialist.  So roughly 13,000 damage points, but this is the same no matter what armor you build and is quite a bit smaller than the hull damage so I will ignore it below.  Keep in mind that the numbers below do not reflect the +20% for the Reinforced Hull device.  All my numbers will be doomstar numbers.<br />
<br />
_______________<br />
Against Distortion Blaster the various armors require the following damage to be destroyed:<br />
<br />
Energy Organic Crystal:  83,776<br />
Wall Of Klein:  40,656<br />
Eternium:  71,148<br />
<br />
_______________<br />
Against Homing Black Holes the various armors require the following damage to be destroyed:<br />
<br />
Energy Organic Crystal:  52,360<br />
Wall Of Klein:  67,760<br />
Eternium:  59,290<br />
<br />
_______________<br />
Against Beam Weapons like Nahodoom Ray Launcher the various armors require the following damage to be destroyed:<br />
<br />
Energy Organic Crystal:  52,360<br />
Wall Of Klein:  67,760<br />
Eternium:  71,148<br />
<br />
<br />
So, in the two weapon categories that matter most HBH and DB we find that Eternium is the middle of the line armor both times.  We also see that Energy Organic Crystal reigns supreme against DB and that Wall Of Klein can take a little less than half that damage but against HBH Wall of Klein is better and Energy Organic Crystal is the worst.<br />
<br />
Most of the ships you will fight will have HBH armaments, but you will have to decide for yourselves which armor works best for your style of play.			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
		  </TR>

		
