			  	Well from what I last heard, the game doesn't use the correct cost to calculate the turns needed for the doom to be built, which is what Cyph was trying to say I believe. If you time the doom building your self, you will see the difference (keep watching the ship pool, and notice when it empties with how much left over)<br />
<br />
Also, one thing I do not believe was factored into that chart was Defence Rating of the armors, which in certain instances may make Eternium the better armor to use against all weapons, including HBH (ie useing Engineering Specialist + Irrational Tactics at lvl 20 vs using Wall of Klien with same abilities)<br />
at the sacrafice of your offensive abilities of course. Just keep those in mind too. 			   <P align=right></P>
